# TODO: Keylet Library Setup & Development

## 1. Project Configuration & Metadata
* [x] Configure development dependencies using `[dependency-groups]` in `pyproject.toml`
  * Add `ruff`, `mypy`, `pytest`, `pytest-cov`, and `types-pyserial` (since `pyserial` lacks inline types)
* [x] Add tool configurations to `pyproject.toml`
  * **Ruff**: Configure linter rules (e.g. `I` for isort, `UP` for pyupgrade, `D` for pydocstyle) and formatter settings
  * **Mypy**: Enable strict type checking and configure overrides (e.g., for `serial`)
  * **Pytest**: Configure test discovery and coverage
* [x] Configure CLI entry point in `pyproject.toml`
  * Add `[project.scripts]` mapping `keylet` to `keylet.bin.cli:main`
* [x] Ensure `py.typed` and resource binaries are correctly packaged by the build backend (`uv_build`)

## 2. CLI Implementation
* [x] Implement `keylet.bin.cli` using `argparse` (or a library like `click` if preferred)
  * `keylet sign [--passphrase <SECRET>] <FILE>` -> writes `<FILE>.signature`
  * `keylet verify [--pubkey <FILE>] <FILE>` -> gets pubkey from file/device, verifies `<FILE>` using `<FILE>.signature`
  * `keylet --output <KEYFILE> pubkey` -> reads pubkey from device, writes to file
  * Implement clean error handling for device connection issues (e.g., `TKeyNotFoundError`)

## 3. Device Binary Storage & Integration
* [x] Add the actual device signer binaries as package resources (e.g., under `src/keylet/resources/`)
* [x] Implement device binary loading in `SignApp`
* [ ] Improve binary loading
  * Add some sort of hash pinning so users can load the exact binary they need
  * Expose loaded device binary version/hash in SignApp

## 4. Testing
* [x] Set up `tests/` directory
* [x] Implement mocked unit tests (no physical device required)
  * Mock serial communication to test protocol framing, application loading, and signing flow
  * Take inspiration from `../securesystemslib/tests/test_tkey_signer.py`
* [x] Implement integration/device-dependent tests
  * Require a test device running a binary built with `no-touch-requirement`
  * Exclude these from default test runs (e.g., using a custom pytest marker like `@pytest.mark.device`)

## 5. CI/CD & Quality Assurance
* [x] Add GitHub Actions workflows (`.github/workflows/`)
